<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1170571243486">
<term>autonomous differential equation</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170571243492">an equation in which the right-hand side is a function of <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> alone</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170571243500">
<term>separable differential equation</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170571243506">any equation that can be written in the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170573742138">
<term>separation of variables</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170573742143">a method used to solve a separable differential equation</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
